text: Fletcher is an unincorporated community in Whitman County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Fletcher was established in 1883, and remained in operation until 1887. The community was named after Joseph Fletcher, the original owner of the town site. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Whitman County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Fletcher, Washington
